
# NAGRUZKA

A simple iOS app for splitting trip expenses with friends — log who paid for what, and see who owes who at the end (or anytime during the trip).

## What it does (v1)

- Create a trip
- Add participants by name
- Log expenses: description, amount, category, who paid, who it's split between
- Predefined categories: Food/Café, Transport, Flights, Accommodation, Activities, Other
- Equal-split calculation across selected participants
- **Balances view** — each person's net position (+ owed to them, − they owe)
- **Settlement view** — minimal "who pays who" list, computed via a greedy debt-simplification algorithm (at most n−1 transactions for n people)

## Planned (not built yet)

- Invite friends via a shareable link (requires a backend)
- Custom split amounts, percentages, or weighted shares
- Multiple payers per expense
- Partial/live settlements ("pay along the way" instead of only at trip end)
- Custom categories
- Multi-currency support

## Tech stack

- **SwiftUI** (iOS)
- **State**: local in-memory only for now — nothing persists between app launches, no sync between devices yet
- **Backend**: not yet chosen — under evaluation between CloudKit (Apple-only, $99/yr dev account), Firebase (free, cross-platform), and Supabase (free with pause-on-inactivity, real Postgres/SQL)


## Status

Early prototype. Local-only — no persistence, no invite links, no backend sync yet.
